								<p>Corey,</p>
<p>Great article!  I&#8217;m applying this to game development where there is a transition from exploring the game mechanics (fun) using Scrum to the production phases where we develop 8-12 hours of assets using a Lean-Kanban approach.  Your description of Scrumban is perfect for transitioning the team.</p>
<p>The main thing that would prevent us from trying Scrumban across the whole project is the concern oflosing a major benefit of the iteration. Preproduction (Scrum) iterations are ideal for a &#8220;unifying audacious goal&#8221; for the team.  We don&#8217;t know all of our tasks (often only 50%), so we leave room in the schedule for exploration.  Leveling development, decoupling iteration planning from review&#8230;this seems to deprecate audacious iteration goals.</p>
